{
  "texts": [
    "Often, by the time feedback is provided, students have already engaged with new material, complicating the task of revisiting, and integrating earlier lessons.",
    "Moreover, conventional feedback tends to be static, offering a one-time view of a student's performance that does not adapt to their ongoing educational needs.",
    "As students advance and their abilities develop, the feedback they once received may no longer be relevant, diminishing its potential to be a powerful tool for learning efficacy.Generative AI could be a catalyst for a significant transformation in how feedback is provided [15,22,37].",
    "In contrast to traditional methods, generative AI, under teacher supervision, can evaluate a student's work in real time, offering immediate feedback alongside the learning process as part of a dynamic learning community.",
    "Take, for instance, the challenging task for beginners of constructing and vocalizing sentences in a new language."
  ]
}